    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that \"tapestry\" thing... it's just temporary. even the stars burn out. if everything is eventually just going to be cold, dark, and empty, then all this effort to find \"meaning\" or \"connection\" is just a coping mechanism to hide the truth. it feels like we're just running on a treadmill for no reason. why bother trying to be a \"vital thread\" if the whole fabric is just going to be destroyed anyway? it feels more like a burden than a gift.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
